<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 3:44PM CDT  by NWS Jackson</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Lowndes
County through 415 PM CDT...
At 344 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Bigbee Valley, or 9 miles south of Columbus, moving
south at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern
Lowndes County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
